As many of you already know, we have officially embarked on building a=20
commercial credit trading business based in Europe but globally focused with=
=20
trading operations in London and Houston.  We are focused on externally=20
launching the business by making two way prices on approximately 200 energy=20
credits in the US, Canada, UK and Nordic markets by 24 Jan. 2000 but we=20
expect to scale up the number of reference credits that we quote on very=20
quickly.  The initial names have been selected and provided to the credit=20
department in both locations for initial review and will be subsequently=20
distributed to the appropriate trading and origination groups for review=20
prior to going live.  The intent is to capture as much of the corporate=20
credit market as possible, as quickly as possible, by leveraging our interna=
l=20
resources (people, processes and systems especially EnronOnline) and the new=
=20
mediums for communication.    To this extent, any ideas that you might have=20
for getting the eyeballs of potential counterparties please let us know. =20

This email marks the first of regular updates on our credit trading=20
initiatives.  We will use this as a mechanism to keep all of you in the loop=
=20
as to where we are in the implementation process and solicit your input on=20
ways to integrate credit products into your existing business models and=20
customer base.

